network_overview: The capture shows control-plane signaling between 5G SMF/UPF (PFCP), 4G MME/SGW (GTPv2-C) and PCRF/HSS (Diameter) with repeated PFCP rule-creation failures and GTP "S1-U Path Failure" indications. No user-plane or voice traffic is observable at this UPF vantage point.

pattern_matches.pattern_name: PFCP Session Establishment - Rule Creation Failure
evidence: Three consecutive failures with different SEIDs
pattern_matches.explanation: Cause value 73 explicitly maps to 'Rule creation/modification Failure', indicating the UPF could not install the PDU session forwarding rules provided by the SMF.

pattern_matches.pattern_name: GTPv2-C Path Failure - S1-U interface down
evidence: Message: Modify Bearer Response (Msg-0x15) and Create Bearer Response (Msg-0x11)
pattern_matches.explanation: GTP Cause 128 is standardized as 'S1-U Path Failure', meaning the SGW cannot reach the eNodeB user-plane endpoint for the requested bearer.

observations.finding: Five PFCP requests (Msg-50) never answered within 27 s
observations.evidence: Seq 852494-852497 plus one heartbeat (Msg-54) also unanswered

observations.finding: 100 % of PFCP Session Establishment attempts failed with cause 73
100 % of GTP Modify/Create Bearer attempts failed with cause 128
observations.evidence: Msg-0x15 and Msg-0x11 both returned S1-U Path Failure

root_causes.issue: UPF unable to install PDU session forwarding rules
root_causes.description: Every PFCP Session Establishment Response carries cause 73 'Rule creation/modification Failure', meaning the UPF rejected the SMF-provided PDRs/FARs/QERs.
root_causes.impact: PDU sessions cannot be established; user-plane traffic is blocked.
root_causes.confidence_justification: Explicit standardized cause code 73 in three consecutive responses

root_causes.issue: S1-U path unreachable between SGW and eNodeB
root_causes.description: SGW returns GTPv2-C cause 128 'S1-U Path Failure' for both Modify Bearer and Create Bearer procedures, indicating downstream user-plane connectivity loss.
root_causes.impact: Bearers cannot carry user-plane traffic; results in silent failure or drop for any attached UE.
root_causes.confidence_justification: Standard cause 128 explicitly signals path failure

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: Whether any user-plane packets actually traversed the GTP-U tunnel
inconclusive_aspects.reason: GTP-U payload not captured at this UPF observation point
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Mirror the N3 or S1-U interface to observe G-PDUs

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: Root reason for UPF rule-install failure
inconclusive_aspects.reason: No vendor-specific IE or log exposed in PFCP
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: UPF debug logs showing resource or configuration issue

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: Health of SIP/IMS and voice service
inconclusive_aspects.reason: SIP, RTP, SDP not present in trace
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Capture on N5/N11 or IMS core interfaces

recommendations.action: Investigate UPF resource availability (memory, CPU, table limits) for rule installation
recommendations.rationale: Three identical cause 73 failures point to a UPF-side resource or configuration problem

recommendations.action: Verify S1-U IP reachability and GTP-U path from SGW to listed eNodeB IP
recommendations.rationale: GTP cause 128 confirms downstream path failure

recommendations.action: Enable PFCP vendor-specific IE logging to obtain detailed rule-reject reason
recommendations.rationale: Standard cause 73 does not reveal which rule attribute failed

session_analysis.signaling_health: PFCP and GTP-C exchanges are orderly but fail functionally: every PDU session attempt rejected by UPF, every bearer attempt rejected by SGW.
session_analysis.user_plane_health: Not observable at this capture point (no GTP-U payload decoded).
session_analysis.voice_quality: Not observable (no RTP or SIP captured).
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Control-plane failures (PFCP rule install, GTP path) predict user-plane unavailability even though user-plane itself is not captured.

    SMF->>UPF: PFCP Establish 0x32 (SEID 0x5a0130)

    SMF->>UPF: PFCP Establish 0x32 (SEID 0x5d0110)
    UPF->>SMF: PFCP Establish 0x33 Cause 73 (Rule creation Failure)
    MME->>SGW: GTP Create Bearer 0x10
    SGW->>MME: GTP Create Bearer 0x11 Cause 128 (S1-U Path Failure)
